The paper deals with the computational complexity of RNA secondary structure design, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problem is motivated by its applications in bioinformatics (cs.BIO) and involves the manipulation of sequences and structures (cs.CG). Finally, the paper presents a negative result, which is often studied in the context of lower bounds (cs.LG).
